==English==
===Etymology===
{{Urd}} and Persian ''chabuk'' meaning a horsewhip through Malay ''tjambok'' through Dutch and Afrikaans ''sambok''.
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}} 
# A stout [[rhinoceros]] or [[hippopotamus]] hide whip.
# Latterly: Any whip.
